Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC, Euratom) No 58/97 of 20 December 1996 concerning structural business statistics(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC, Euratom) No 410/98(2), and in particular Articles 12(ii), (v) and (vii) thereof,
(1) Whereas Regulation (EC, Euratom) No 58/97 established a common framework for the production of Community statistics on the structure, activity, performance and competitiveness of the insurance sector in the Community;
(2) Whereas it is necessary to specify the frequency for the compilation of the multi-yearly insurance services statistics; whereas it is necessary to specify the first reference year for the compilation of the results laid down in the Annex 5 to Regulation (EC, Euratom) No 58/98; whereas it is necessary to specify the breakdown of the results for the production of insurance services statistics;
(3) Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the Statistical Programme Committee,
